    {
      "kind": "parameters",
      "parameters": [
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "A workgroup containing one or more threads, including the current thread. If the current thread is not part of this workgroup, this function aborts the process.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "wg"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "The ideal time at which you expect the threads to complete the task for the current interval. The system uses this parameter to assess whether your threads finish early, on-time, or later than expected. Specify this value using the time units of the workgroup. For a list of possible time units, see ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.os/documentation/os/os_clockid_t",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text": ". This value must be greater than the value in the ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "code": "start",
                  "type": "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text": " parameter.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "deadline"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "Additional interval data. Specify ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "code": "NULL",
                  "type": "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text": " for this parameter.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "data"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "return-value",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Return Value",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "A value of ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "0",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " on success, or a nonzero error code indicating why the function failed. Common error codes include ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "EINVAL",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " or ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "EPERM",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ". For example, this method returns ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "EINVAL",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " if you didn’t start the workgroup.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Call this function between calls to the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.os/documentation/os/os_workgroup_interval_start",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " and ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.os/documentation/os/os_workgroup_interval_finish",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " functions. Typically, you call it at regular intervals to set a new deadline for any ongoing work. For example, after delivering content for the current video frame, call this function to set the deadline for finishing the next video frame. Call this function only once for each new interval. If your workgroup contains multiple threads, designate one thread to start, stop, and update the group.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "This function returns an error if you created the workgroup using the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.os/documentation/os/os_workgroup_create_with_workgroup",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " or ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.os/documentation/os/os_workgroup_create_with_port",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " function. This function works only on workgroups that you create using the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "os_workgroup_interval_create",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " function.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
